cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.LG 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze large-scale collections of tweets related to events. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and Bayesian inference, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model quantitatively and qualitatively, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
